body:
This simple diff fixes the segfault:

```diff
diff --git a/src/couch/priv/couch_js/60/main.cpp b/src/couch/priv/couch_js/60/main.cpp
index c92cfb7c9..ecedfbd3b 100644
--- a/src/couch/priv/couch_js/60/main.cpp
+++ b/src/couch/priv/couch_js/60/main.cpp
@@ -487,8 +487,5 @@ main(int argc, const char* argv[])
         JS_MaybeGC(cx);
     }
 
-    JS_DestroyContext(cx);
-    JS_ShutDown();
-
     return 0;
 }
```

hey @davisp , @wohali  , @janl , after some investigation, I highly suspect that this `"out of memory"` is related to `infinite_loop` test in https://github.com/apache/couchdb/blob/master/test/javascript/tests/view_errors.js#L154
```
      var designDoc3 = {
        _id:"_design/infinite",
        language: "javascript",
        views: {
          "infinite_loop" :{map:"function(doc) {while(true){emit(doc,doc);}};"}
        }
      };
      T(db.save(designDoc3).ok);

      try {
          db.view("infinite/infinite_loop");
          T(0 == 1);
      } catch(e) {
          T(e.error == "os_process_error" || e.error == "unnamed_error");
      }
```

The sequence of test suites follows `view_errors.js` and then `view_include_docs.js`. In some case, `couchjs` is shared among different test suites. After `view_errors` bumped memory, there is no room for `view_include_docs.js` to allocate when the shared `couchjs` is used.

Today, I ever made several test in docker image
1. run `make javascript suites="view_include_docs"` more than 200 times in the loop, and didn't hit out-of-memory issue
2. run `make javascript suites="view_errors  view_include_docs"`, and i can get out-of-memory sometime, like

```
root@0010847bf784:/couchdb# make javascript suites="view_errors  view_include_docs"
test/javascript/tests/view_errors.js         pass
test/javascript/tests/view_include_docs.js
    Error: (new String("out of memory")) (function (doc) { if (typeof doc.integer === 'number') {emit(doc.integer, doc.integer)};})
Trace back (most recent call first):

 551:14: test/javascript/couch.js
      CouchError
 514:12: test/javascript/couch.js
      CouchDB.maybeThrowError
 202:5: test/javascript/couch.js
      CouchDB/this.view
 43:14: test/javascript/tests/view_include_docs.js
      couchTests.view_include_docs
 45:5: test/javascript/cli_runner.js
      runTest
 56:1: test/javascript/cli_runner.js

fail
=======================================================
JavaScript tests complete.
  Failed: 1.  Skipped or passed: 1.
make: *** [Makefile:279: javascript] Error 1
```

3. run `make javascript suites="view_errors  view_include_docs"` after commenting out below in `view_errors.js`. I didn't see out-of-memory when running more than 100 times 
```
      try {
          db.view("infinite/infinite_loop");
          T(0 == 1);
      } catch(e) {
          //T(e.error == "os_process_error" || e.error == "unnamed_error");
      }
```

Could we give me a try in Jenkins server to disable infinite_loop temporarily?
